The paper deals with the problem of layering directed graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem is also related to graph theory (cs.DS) and combinatorial optimization (cs.DM). The authors mention that their approach involves minimizing a weighted sum of various factors, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of optimization (cs.GT). Finally, the authors present computational experiments, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of simulation and modeling (cs.SI).
